      "writtenOn": "2020-12-17T16:53:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Not yet. As soon as I implement calls to functions that weren\u0027t (yet) inlined, there are writes to globals, or to \u0027out\u0027 variables. The path forward on that stuff is pretty straightforward, I think - just recursively emitting the code for each function at the call site (much like sample-child, etc.). But I\u0027ll need to turn the return stuff into a stack, and fold it into mask() to avoid these kinds of side effects.",
